Your `while` statement is the problem. It&#39;s using the comma expression, which is not what you want because it ends up evaluating finally to &#39;X&#39;. You need to compare `f` to each of your options separately.

One way to accomplish this is to expand the comparison in the `while` statement to something like

```c++
while (f != &#39;A&#39; &amp;&amp; f != &#39;S&#39; &amp;&amp; f != &#39;D&#39; &amp;&amp; f != &#39;M&#39; &amp;&amp; f != &#39;X&#39;)
{
  ...
}
```
The same is true for your `if` statement a few lines below.

The problem with your code is that the logic is not inside the while loop that is why it cannot go through the necessary if and else, so I edited your code and applied some changes.

